<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 12:09PM EDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog Possible Near the Lake into the Afternoon...
As of 11 AM, an area of fog was expanding southward toward the
northwest Indiana lakeshore. Patchy dense fog with visibility of
one quarter mile or less may push into areas along the shore and
just inland, with the foggy conditions lasting through the early
afternoon if the fog does come ashore. If you will be driving near
the lake, you may encounter sharply reduced visibility in spots.</description>
